cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.DS, cs.SY, cs.LG. 

This paper deals with discrete logarithm computation in finite fields, which is a fundamental problem in cryptography. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves algorithms and complexity analysis, which suggests that it could belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of subfields and the reduction of the width and height of the descent tree indicate that it could also be classified under cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.LG (Machine Learning).
